{"TopicId":190283,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"About plane design","CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T08:04:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T08:04:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTarget: design a highly maneuverable plane with conventional layout (2 vertical and 2 horizontal tails with 2 main wings)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E: Yes\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E \u0026amp; \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E: the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is only a bit forward than \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E, the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E is within the sphere of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nProblem: when flying, control the plane to rise its head will cause of trembling (up and down) head.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPS: I\u0027ve already turned off the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAoA\u003C/abbr\u003E and pitch \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E given by\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR, but the stock \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is on.\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nGuess: The torque given by main wings is larger than that given by control-surface when the speed dropping down (which is cause by stalling)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnyone has idea about this? Did someone once encountered this problem?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-10T08:57:56Z\u0022 title=\u002212/10/2019 08:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 10, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Scrooge\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Incarnation of Chaos","CreatedById":197414,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T08:50:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCanards for extra pitch control are generally helpful if you\u0027re going for a inherently unstable design like this, but make sure to set the control limits so \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t freak out and cause noodling.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T08:54:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223715614\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190283\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575967849\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Incarnation of Chaos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Incarnation of Chaos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCanards for extra pitch control are generally helpful if you\u0027re going for a inherently unstable design like this, but make sure to set the control limits so \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t freak out and cause noodling.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCanards have positive feedback when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAoA\u003C/abbr\u003E is larger so I think it\u0027s a good idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I am still curious about how this kind of phenomenon occurs, well, maybe it\u0027s not because of lift of main wings but the reverse torque given by \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T09:12:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201766-scrooge/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022201766\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201766-scrooge/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scrooge\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve moved your topic to gameplay questions as it is a question about gameplay.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T09:13:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223715621\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190283\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575969140\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160462\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, James Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201766-scrooge/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022201766\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201766-scrooge/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scrooge\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve moved your topic to gameplay questions as it is a question about gameplay.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you very much!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T11:27:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9100620086\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://www.reddit.com/r/SimplePlanes/comments/5cr5te/shakingrocking_whenever_i_pitch_updown/\u0022 style=\u0022height:262px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngot an answer perfectly solve my puzzle.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be honest, I\u0027ve tried moving \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E backward until the aircraft was\u00A0nearly static-unstable, but the improvement is limited.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will try reduce angles of every control surfaces, and see how it goes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-10T11:42:23Z\u0022 title=\u002212/10/2019 11:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 10, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Scrooge\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-10T19:32:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPress CAPS LOCK to turn it on. Your input will be smoother on the control surfaces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UncleManuel","CreatedById":201419,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-14T19:43:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223715600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190283\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575965058\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201766\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scrooge\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/10/2019 at 9:04 AM, Scrooge said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTarget: design a highly maneuverable plane with conventional layout (2 vertical and 2 horizontal tails with 2 main wings)\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck the assignment (right click) of each control surface. By default all axis are turned on. I found the planes hard to control once they are in a stall spin, with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E centered or slight in front. The \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E has no chance of regaining control nor manual control (keyboard or XBOX-Controller for Windows)...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ph34r.png\u0022 title=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said please note that KSP ist not a very accurate simulation of aerodynamics...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-14T21:55:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223717332\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190283\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221576352585\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201419\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UncleManuel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, UncleManuel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck the assignment (right click) of each control surface. By default all axis are turned on. I found the planes hard to control once they are in a stall spin, with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E centered or slight in front. The \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E has no chance of regaining control nor manual control (keyboard or XBOX-Controller for Windows)...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ph34r.png\u0022 title=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 width=\u002220\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said please note that KSP ist not a very accurate simulation of aerodynamics...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022 width=\u002220\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00227D636B4AEC1A2EE20A679F707A5B8C35A04FB6E7\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/792002086715911498/7D636B4AEC1A2EE20A679F707A5B8C35A04FB6E7/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002207F3D27A9F5EFF0B022DA656CA0FF75F38DDF4B4\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/792002086715910783/07F3D27A9F5EFF0B022DA656CA0FF75F38DDF4B4/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022571AB7ABFC31386A094DAE4EC759562DCD29BB96\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/792002086715909855/571AB7ABFC31386A094DAE4EC759562DCD29BB96/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, you are right, but I found it easy when you add exceeded control torque to fully cancel\u00A0the fixed torque, then your plane can go any \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAoA\u003C/abbr\u003E you want...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI add TV engine (Panther), 2 reaction wheel, 40 degree control surfaces...and now, the plane can go stall and do\u00A0Frolov\u0027s\u00A0Chakra at a speed below 100m/s\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHigh \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E make it quick to recover speed, I think I seize some inspiration, but I haven\u0027t figure the system out...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-14T21:57:08Z\u0022 title=\u002212/14/2019 09:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 14, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Scrooge\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}